data.name: instructions1Label.Text
data.value:
Currently, there is no free method to use this program.
I am working on an app for the Google Play Store and the iOS App Store that will implement this feature. For now, you just have to find an app that allows sending UDP Packets.
When the app you choose asks for the IP Address and the port, enter the information found below the source code link. After you enter the information, below is a list of all the commands you can send to your PC.

data.name: instructions2Label.Text
data.value:
Note: these commands are case sensitive. Also, make sure you send packets as a string, and using the UDP port, not the TCP port.
1. shutdown (This command shuts down your PC) 2. lock (This command locks your PC) 3. restart (This command restarts your PC) 4. test (This command shows a message on the PC. This is mainly used for testing the connection)
